The paper focuses on point cloud upsampling using Graph Convolutional Networks (GCNs), which is a popular technique in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of multi-scale feature extractors, which is a common topic in computer graphics (cs.GR) and natural language processing (cs.CL). Additionally, the paper proposes novel point upsampling modules, which is a topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
